            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.03309.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
           
            <ab>Sept. 1, 1871.</ab>
            <ab>Hon. Hamilton Fish,</ab>
            <ab>Secretary of State.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I am directed by the President to request you to issue a commission appointing J. H. Wickizer to the office of Attorney of the United States for Utah Territory, in place of C. H. Hempstead, resigned.</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully, &amp;c.</ab>
            <ab>A. T. Akerman,</ab>
            <ab>Attorney General.</ab>
            
            <note type="authorial" place="left" rend="none">Commission</note>
            
        </body>
